ost sense!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering serialization techniques**\\n\\nI'm thinking about replacing an object with a proxy that implements IndirectlySerialized. This might mean that during the same streaming serialization, the proxy fields could get serialized too. It doesn’t involve mapping, which is a good point. There’s definitely a lot to consider here regarding how proxies and serialization work together, and I want to make sure I'm getting this right for future tasks. It’s fascinating how these details can change the outcomes!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8wbeDHQ1MJaFSM1YeAdcjSpU|fc_0653e50b39646f870169f2d06ba7b8819495c09127061c7600", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"sourceCompatibility|JavaVersion|languageVersion\" -n build.gradle tests/src/com.mchange/c3p0/0.9.5.4/build.gradle gradle.properties"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"rg \\\"sourceCompatibility|JavaVersion|languageVersion\\\" -n build.gradle tests/src/com.mchange/c3p0/0.9.5.4/build.gradle gradle.properties\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3456, "output": 2126, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34766, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777520719706, "responseId": "resp_0653e50b39646f870169f2d05049f48194a7ee88a8597c2cac"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_8wbeDHQ1MJaFSM1YeAdcjSpU|fc_0653e50b39646f870169f2d06ba7b8819495c09127061c7600", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "(no output)\n\nCommand exited with code 1"}], "details": {}, "isError": true, "timestamp": 1777520748203}]}
